**State whether each equation is true or false:**

[\log_8 (x - 3) = \log_8 x - \log_8 3] — False, because [\log_8 (x - 3) \neq \log_8 x - \log_8 3] unless [x - 3 = \frac{x}{3}].

[\log_5 22x = \log_5 22 + \log_5 x] — True, by the Product Property.

[\log_{10} 19k = 19 \log_{10} k] — False, because [\log 19k \neq 19 \log k]; the 19 multiplies the logarithm of k, not the argument.

[\log_2 y^5 = 5 \log_2 y] — True, by the Power Property.

[\log_7 \frac{x}{3} = \log_7 x - \log_7 3] — True, by the Quotient Property.

[\log_4 (z + 2) = \log_4 z + \log_4 2] — False, because [\log_4 (z + 2) \neq \log_4 z + \log_4 2] unless [z + 2 = 2z].

[\log_8 p^4 = (\log_8 p)^4] — False, because [4 \log_8 p \neq (\log_8 p)^4].

[\log_9 \frac{x^2 y^3}{z^4} = 2 \log_9 x + 3 \log_9 y - 4 \log_9 z] — True, by the Product, Quotient, and Power Properties.

